-- Irish house price rises spread beyond Dublin
-- 
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 06:23AM EDT
-- None



DUBLIN, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Irish house prices outside Dublin grew at their fastest rate in seven years with an increase of 5 percent in the year to July, up from 3 percent a month ago in a sign the market recovery is starting to move beyond the capital, data showed on Wednesday.

Prices for residential property in Dublin surged 23 percent in the year to July, down slightly from 24 percent a month ago.